&quot;X buff for 40pp donation!&quot; or something on a similar line.  Go back to your english lessons people... it isn't a donation then!  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=valkyriebuffinstuff@firionavie>Valkyrie Buffinstuff</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/27/03 11:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4113.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   /shrug</span><hr size=1> It's all semantics.<br>
<br>
Saying &quot;donate to be targetted for group&quot; sounds vastly better than saying &quot;Give plat to be targetted for group.&quot;  Though I have seen some folks who say &quot;Casting Temp for 20pp, Virtue for 40pp at Nexus stone, open trade window to be targetted for group.&quot;<br>
<br>
While someone *could&quot; say, I suppose, that this person is more &quot;truthful&quot; or &quot;gramattically correct&quot; than the person asking for &quot;donations&quot; ... who cares?<br>
<br>
For every shout of &quot;I am casting 'X' spell for plat&quot; in PoK that I see, there are no less than three &quot;Donating 'X' amount of plat for 'X' buff, PST.&quot;  Where there is demand, there is supply.<br>
<br>
Personally I could care less if someone is paying to make their leveling faster or easier ... more power to them.  Nor do I care if someone would like to make a profit off their hard earned abilities (yes, spells and the levels required to cast them *are* hard earned) - heck a lot of the people I've known who cast KEI and/or Virtue in PoK for plat are either making up the exhorbitant price they paid for the spell in question OR saving up the exhorbitant sum they will have to pay for the upgrade (VoQ, HoV). <br>
<br>
&quot;Selling&quot; buffs is hardly a crime.  It does not make the dumb people less dumb or the good players any better.  The only drawback I can see to it is the inevitable pestering other casters whose services are not for sale will endure ... and honestly, I don't think someone rude enough to pester someone for buffs out of the blue would care if it was a regular practice to sell buffs or not ... they would still be a pest.<br>
<br>
