<br>
At level 10, when people first start going into Crushbone, characters with normal gear have roughly a few hundred hitpoints, no more than 400 at best. So, at level 10 Prum can heal for what? 30hit points per cast? 33 with his healing I helm. <br>
<br>
Now, with Temp, that 400 hitpoints goes well over 1K. With that many hitpoints, people would pull non-stop. Im talking, 5-6 reds per pull, get beat down to almost dead and expect Prum to heal em back to full. I had many groups get Prum killed during his time in Crushbone because they all had temp and thought themselves unkillable. <br>
<br>
A level limit on Temp would be a good idea. Maybe not 45, make it 30. But before 30 you shouldnt NEED temp to make it through a group session. Those casters who NEEDED KEI in thier 20s-30s before it was removed didnt know thier class. Prum doesnt need KEI. He doesnt need clarity. I know how to play the class. <br>
