<br>
Most chanters that I have spoke to request a donation to be invited for targeting purposes.  They will indeed accept anything with no minimum in most cases, and if asked politely will happily invite you if you are on a CR.<br>
<br>
If you want KEI, you donate.  Same as if you want you car washed by a bunch of cheerleaders, you reach into your wallet, same as if you want to be a member in good standing of your church, you fill those pretty donation envelopes they send you with some greenbacks.<br>
<br>
it is a donation until they specifically say they are selling x for x amount.  Look at fund raising car washes.  They can even say they require a donation of 10$.  You are not paying to have your car washed.  You are donating to their cause, and in return they are washing your car.  Think of it that way.  You are donating to the enchanters cause, and in return they are blessing you with KEI.  You are not buying KEI.<br>
<br>
Personally, I am much happier with chanters asking for donations, allowing me to give what I can (which is usually a nice healthy sum, but sometimes I am a bit short) rather than bluntly saying &quot;Selling KEI, 50pp.&quot; <br>
<br>
*shrugs* <p>~Wolf/Ssakas/Jr/Whatever</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dalliancefv>DallianceFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>WTFeth!</span><br>  Posts: 319<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/28/03 4:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4113.topic&index=14>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /shrug</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>So the donation is a nice thing to do, because you are paying for that caster's time and effort. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
